	   <tr><td colspan=2>There are a few possibilites as to why your dots are being resisted more than your dds.  <br>1. The resistance of the mobs you are killing.  It is not unusual for a mob to have a higher resist for sickness and poision than for cold.  <br><br>2. I'm not sure about this one, but I remember hearing/reading something about skill lvl playing a roll in weather a spell is resisted.  Just like it does for weapons.  Since you have been using dd and not using dot, it is safe to assume  that your conguring skill is not as high as your evocation skill.  This being the case your dots will be resisted more than your dd.  <br><br>In the end those telling you it is better to use dot are right.  You kill more mobs for the same amount of mana and have less down time.  On the other hand I know a shaman who is soloing at lvl 45 using mostly dd.  <br><br>Hopes this helps;<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
