	   <tr><td colspan=2>I consider Invigor a 'stamina regen'.  I keep it loaded when my group is power pulling or working on a mob with an unusually high number of hp's.  That way when one of the tanks says they're "running out of yellow"  I can hit them quickly. Also, upon joining a group, I ask the tanks in the group if anyone has the stamina problem (wood elves, for instance, seem to have less stamina than other races).<br><br>Spirit of Cheetah.  I have used this spell all of one time.  My eight memmed spell slots are always filled with spells I need for a given situation.  I guess you might say I am one of those who say it is a bother and ineffective.  It isn't worth it to me to lose a spell slot for 40 seconds of speed that can only be recast about every ten or fifteen minutes.<br><br>Scale of Wolf, on the other hand, is something that I do use when running long distances.  Like Cheetah, it shuts off if you attack or cast, but I consider Scale a travelling spell, and don't use it if there is chance I may be aggro'd enroute.<br>&nbsp;<br>Badjur Bravehartt<br>52 Mystic of Druzzil Ro<br>Tar Valon</td></tr>
