	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am one of the many disgruntled wizzy wannabes, who have switched, in frustration, to being a Shammy.And let me tell you that the ever changing and enigmatic world called Norrath has never seemed so fresh and vibrant to me.I have had to learn to actually use my brain when preparing for combat, and during the actual engagement. No more, Root-Nuke, Root-Nuke, blah, blah, blah, etc, etc, ad nauseam.I'm having fun again and I'm bound and determined to become the best Shammy possible. I am, as of now, only 20 seasons and still feel like I'm learning all the nuances and subtleties of being a productive member of any group kind enough(or smart enough)to have me. I will appreciate any advice you venerable Shammies can give to a relative newcomer in this field. My request for advice is a little vague, so let me clarify. I am, by most standards, a semi-intelligent person (lady) and I understand that in a group I cant acquiesce to everyone's demands for this buff and that. I think I know which buffs will benefit which class in the group, and it's pretty clear to me that if there is no other healer in the group then I am best served by buffing myself and the tank, and healing said tank. I mention buffing myself first because I figure that if I'm not around to try and heal the tank, because one or two buffs I should have casted on myself I casted elsewhere to please others, then I've failed at my job. I was in my first group in SK the other night, camping Gnolls, and there was a Druid in the group. I told him that I would buff the tank, a Monk in this instance, with everything I could, but would he, the Druid, mind casting Skin Like Rock on the tank also. Well, as you all know, everyone wants a SoW. Everyone wants whatever they can get, although the buffs or mana would be better spent elsewhere. At least at times it appears this way. There was little regard for the Monk, and if there was going to be enough mana to buff and heal her. When mana is at a premium shouldnt the tank take first priority? Especially a tank that has questionable armor and no natural hp enhancements? The other three members, by the way, were pure casters. If the tank died while pulling 2 Gnolls we'd be slaughtered unless we could reach Infected Paw to zone. I feel as if I made no friends that night, save the Monk, who spoke to me in tells. Should I have kept my mouth shut? Should I have just done whatever the majority wanted me to do, even if it seemed tactically unsound to me? Like I said, I'm still new at this and I know I dont have all the answers. I'm smart enough to know that there are others out there much smarter than myself. If I KNOW I'm in the right then I will say so or leave the group or both. Perhaps there was a better and more efficient manner in which I should have rationed the mana. If so, please tell me. I'm a proud and tenacious Lady Barbarian Shaman. Please help me to become a better one :o)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
