	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm a 45th shaman. I normally look for a group with a primary healer. So I can do what shaman do best buff/debuff.<br><br>When in a full group with a primary healer I first and formost keep sow on everyone. I keep tanks buffed to the max (sta, agi, dex, str, ac, hp) I will keep regen on the puller since they need the extra healing while pulling.<br><br>The main trick I have found is I give myself a buff before any of the tanks. Not because I need the buff but I need a good timmer as to when the buffs are starting to go. So I can rebuff myself and the tanks in the group. I play a lot and in most cases of many hours playing the tanks don't have to ask for any buff more than once or twice. If you keep them buffed and time it where you have about 5 mins between when 1 buff runs out and the next one will. You can normally keep 40 mana avial for backup heals. Going this route I'm also able to slow the mob's, and keep quick/Alacrity going on the tanks. <br><br>This method has made friends of all mele types that I have ever grouped with. So I find in many cases I barily log in and get tells for groups even keeping ano up.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
