	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.12]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just a comment  on the "An ogre at 75% of his HP all the time can still have more HP than a troll at full health."  <br><br>The base difference in Stamnina, hence hp, for ogres and trolls is 13 points.  At level 50, that MIGHT give you 30 more hp.  Just wanted everyone to know that those 13 stamina are NOT going to make that much off a difference, especially at the beginning.<br><br>Trolls get regen, which means you can cannabilize more often.  Ogres can't be stunned from a physical attack from the front, which means less interrupts if channel pulls through.  Which is better to you is more of a playstyle choice, although at higher levels, the need to be able to cast through a bash is rare.<br><br>Just to let you know, I play a barbarian.  He was one of my first characters, back when banded was not heard of, and I was scared to death to play an evil guy (aka faction was more important to me than either regen or no stun).  If I had to do it again, I would probably lean towards either an Iksar or Troll, just for the regen.<br><br>Gorthin Spiritcaller<br>51 Shaman BB<br>Chugrahk <br>20 SK BB<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
